From 1d3dd86a9dcda170d65543ad873cc1ce8f8b73d0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jan Martens <44572196+JanMa@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 22:07:15 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 16/22] Cleanup Ember Mixins in UI (#2465)

* log all ember deprecations

Cleaning them up is a prerequisite of updating EmberJS to later versions

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup FocusOnInsertMixin

move the functionality in the components using it

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup WithNavToNearestAncestor mixin

move the code to the single controller using it

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup ModelBoundaryRoute mixin

And move the cleanup logic in the routes using it

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup KeyMixin

And move the logic into the secret and lease models which used it

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup ListRoute mixin

and move it in the routes using it

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup ListController mixin

and move it into the controllers using it

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup UnloadModel mixin

And move the logic into the controller. One gnarly route for
backend/secret-edit.js still needs cleanup

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup UnloadModelMixin in backend/secret/edit route

The ugly way by just inlining the mixin code into the route and
sprinkling some eslint-disable statements. In all other route we did it
the proper way by moving the cleanup logic into the controller and
calling it in resetController, but I couldn't get this to work reliabily
for this route.

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup BackendCrumb mixin

And move the logic into the controller

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup ClusterRoute mixin

And move it into a dedicated base route for reuse

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

* cleanup UnsavedModelRoute mixin

And move the logic into the routes

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>

---------

Signed-off-by: Jan Martens <jan@martens.eu.org>
Signed-off-by: Aditya <jaiswal.aditya.deelip@gmail.com>
